TI  - The U-Curve Adjustment Hypothesis Revisited: A Review and Theoretical Framework
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 225
EP  - 247
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
AB  - The cross-cultural adjustment research literature has largely been conducted from an atheoretical perspective. When a theoretical framework is imposed, the U-Curve adjustment theory has been the one most commonly used. The lack of a comprehensive review of the empirical literature on the U-Curve adjustment theory has allowed scholars to accept or dismiss the theory on grounds other than that of empirical evidence. This paper reviews the empirical literature and proposes a theoretical framework and research agenda for future research on cross-cultural adjustment.
